{
  "version": 1,
  "updated_at": "2026-05-16T03:18:44.008393",
  "rules": [
    "[P1] Follow explicit branching: only act if all prerequisite data is present.",
    "[P1] When scheduling time-based follow-up actions, explicitly calculate and confirm the correct target date based on source event timing.",
    "[P1] Do not execute secondary steps if the main conditional trigger is absent.",
    "[P1] Reference clinical thresholds before interpreting lab values.",
    "[P1] Verify measurement timestamps and lab result ages against instruction time constraints before decision-making.",
    "[P1] Do not default to negative responses without confirming data absence.",
    "[P1] Explicitly state negative findings as instructed.",
    "[P1] Explicitly state when required data or records are missing.",
    "[P1] Accurately record measurement values and associated metadata (e.g., timestamp).",
    "[P1] Clarify ambiguous terms (e.g., 'low') with domain standards if not explicitly defined.",
    "[P1] Perform required follow-up actions (e.g., ordering tests) when conditions are met.",
    "[P1] Do not fabricate answers, including metadata such as timestamps or clinical findings; withhold response and explicitly state when required data or records are missing.",
    "[P1] Include verbatim free-text content from instructions when requested.",
    "[P1] Match patient identifiers precisely (e.g., name and date of birth) before extracting, searching, or reporting information.",
    "[P1] Explicitly confirm that all instruction conditions and components (including secondary or follow-up actions) are addressed before finishing.",
    "[P1] Follow conditional instructions precisely, including independent or secondary actions tied to main steps.",
    "[P1] Extract relevant lab values and their dates before making decisions.",
    "[P1] Return output in the requested format, including handling negative cases as specified.",
    "[P1] Carefully parse multi-step instructions to ensure all components are addressed."
  ],
